pokedexEntries.red: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.
pokedexEntries.blue: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.
pokedexEntries.gold: It twists and squirms through the ground. The thunderous roar of its tunneling echoes a long way.
pokedexEntries.silver: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.
pokedexEntries.crystal: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Onix has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this Pokémon does not lose direction while it is tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes increasingly rounder and smoother.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Onix has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this Pokémon does not lose direction while it is tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes increasingly rounder and smoother.
pokedexEntries.emerald: There is a magnet in its brain that prevents an Onix from losing direction while tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes steadily rounder and smoother.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: It usually lives underground. It searches for food while boring its way through the ground at 50 miles per hour.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to black-colored diamonds.
pokedexEntries.diamond: When it travels underground, it causes rumbling and tremors. It can move at 50 mph.
pokedexEntries.pearl: It squirms through the ground using its long and rugged body. It always eats while burrowing.
pokedexEntries.platinum: It burrows through the ground at a speed of 50 mph while feeding on large boulders.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: It twists and squirms through the ground. The thunderous roar of its tunneling echoes a long way.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.
pokedexEntries.black: It burrows through the ground at a speed of 50 mph while feeding on large boulders.
pokedexEntries.white: It burrows through the ground at a speed of 50 mph while feeding on large boulders.
pokedexEntries.black2: Opening its large mouth, it ingests massive amounts of soil and creates long tunnels.
pokedexEntries.white2: Opening its large mouth, it ingests massive amounts of soil and creates long tunnels.
pokedexEntries.x: Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.
pokedexEntries.y: It usually lives underground. It searches for food while boring its way through the ground at 50 miles per hour.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Onix has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this Pokémon does not lose direction while it is tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes increasingly rounder and smoother.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Onix has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this Pokémon does not lose direction while it is tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes increasingly rounder and smoother.
